##I spent 72 hours in a support group | Wuhan People 1

Over the past few days, I have watched these Wuhan people coalesce in a way that almost burns them, and fight against the constant turbulence and lack of external support, limited by their own power, we finally have to choose to compromise to the reality.
By Li Jiayu
Editor | Luo Lixuan

No one wants to save the city more than the people of Wuhan.

After the Lihan passage was closed, they moved quickly to tell the story of Wuhan and to try to save the isolated city.

Caring car owners were one of the first groups to receive media attention. Their appearance, originally was to solve the problem of the medical staff's travel difficulty after the hasty "closure of the city" , in the supporting program before the introduction, through this window period. If it weren't for them, many of the front line health care workers would either not be able to go home or would have to walk or share bicycles.

When I joined the travel support group, I was just looking for an interview. But as an ordinary person who is far away from the front line, I really want to do something for these kind people. So I really became a volunteer, and we use stupid way to build a loose "bridge" , so that the medical staff through a temporary way to the front.

There were many such aid groups in Wuhan at the time, and their goodwill was admirable, but should not be wasted. Over the past few days, I have watched these Wuhan people coalesce in a way that is almost self-immolating, and join them in fighting against the constant upheavals and lack of external support, constrained by their limited personal power, we finally have to choose to compromise to the reality.

I don't write to sing, because in many ways, a hero doesn't have to be a hero.

Bypass

The closure of the city was swift and alarming compared with the apparently imprompt notification of the outbreak.

In an interview, Zhou Xianwang, Wuhan's mayor, said Wuhan was "very decisive" in some tough measures. But he did not mention that the city of tens of millions of people had been thrown into unexpected trouble by the rush to shut down the city.

Public transport was suspended, hospitals were short of beds, staff and supplies, face masks and alcohol were hard to come by, and even meat and vegetables, the staples of everyday life, were hard to come by. Although commercial forces including Alibaba, Meituan and Didi quickly announced their involvement, they were unable to fill the gap left by the government's supporting measures.

The issue of medical staff travel was the first to erupt. Many of the front-line workers in the country's war against the disease rely on public transport to get to work and can only ride shared bikes or walk to hospitals on the day. This bizarre and extreme situation infuriated many people and became an accelerant for Wuhan people to save themselves.

REAKA is one of a number of people who have started initiatives on platforms such as Weibo to form a team of caring drivers. She was a doctor, because not in the first-line department, these days have been at home waiting for arrangements. Early on the morning of the 23rd, after seeing the news of the closing of the Han Dynasty Channel, she was so anxious that she could not sleep. "If the medical staff can not arrive at their posts or can not be on time, who will treat the patient? "

Two-dimensional code of Mutual Aid Group for medical staff on Weibo

So, Reaka also set up a QQ group for medical travel mutual assistance. She only posted qr codes in her friends'circles and in a few groups, but Abelian Group's popularity grew. She thought, there should be a lot of people to help do voluntary publicity, "it also shows that the demand is really big. "

I joined the medical travel support group on New Year's Eve. At first, I just wanted to contact and interview some Wuhan citizens through these QQ groups and wechat groups. But as Reaka scoured the messages again and again for volunteers, I couldn't help but think that there was something I could do without being on the front lines.

After a brief interaction with Reaka, I became a group administrator and was drawn into the group. The eight administrators who were in the group at the time, Reaka found them temporarily in the group. What we need to do is remind them repeatedly to change their notes and teach them how to post travel requests and "take orders" as medical staff and car owners (and, of course, "irrelevant people" like me) keep coming in.

That was a pretty rough start. Abelian group's applications kept coming up, and REAKA had to temporarily top up QQ's annual membership, raising the QQ group's maximum membership to 2,000.

The first thing to deal with is the question of authenticity. In the face of the incessant requests from Abelian group, we were unable or unable to verify their identities or qualifications, so we had to post a bulletin in the group to remind the owners and the doctors to show each other their identification documents in advance of docking. There is a risk, it seems, that in a time like this, any whiff of malevolence could hurt those on the front lines.

In the beginning, we used online documentation to tally travel requirements, but the general, primitive approach to message boards was too inefficient. At one point, we switched to online Excel  forms that let doctors and car owners fill out their own travel needs or free time, but that didn't seem like a good idea either.

The dialog box is still noisy, the number is still increasing, and soon after the new method, someone proposed to separate management of car owners and medical care, by the administrator unified send and receive messages.

We had a fight about it. Some felt that it would be too inefficient to let them match themselves, while others felt that separate management would add to the existing workload.

A strange feeling of tension clenched behind him. We all worried that the repeated changes in the method would delay the travel of medical staff, and finally decided by voting to divert the car owners and medical staff to two QQ groups, with the administrator acting as a relay station for information.

Horn is in this time because speak up and gradually assume the role of "commander. ". The Wuhan girl is studying at a university in Beijing. The last thing she worries about recently is whether she will graduate on time after the school has been postponed. Under her command, several people began to divide the group drainage and docking information.

It was New Year's Eve. I wasn't always online. At PM, I went back online after dinner and was surprised to find that a complete process had started running.

The 2,000-person medical team is already full, and a 500-person motorist team has been set up. Medical will travel needs private chat sent to an administrator, administrator finishing, number and then forward to the owner group. Every once in a while, someone is responsible for putting the list left in the chat record into a table by region and time, and then uploading it to the QQ group.

When I went online, the group's most recent list number was 132, which means we had already passed on travel requests to at least 132 health care workers. In addition to sending and receiving information, managers should regularly remind car owners to pay attention to safety, do a good job wearing masks, frequently disinfection and other protective measures.


In a short afternoon, these strangers who come together for a common goal have formed a well-organized travel service team, running out of a set of pipeline, systematic operation mode. Everyone together with the stupid way to build a manual "medical travel platform. ".

Of course, not every list is claimed by its owner, and some people wait a long time before deciding to ride a shared bike to and from work on their own. But you can't blame the owners for that. No matter how many people are moving at the same time, the power of the individual is limited. They try their best, but also can only build a loose "bridge. ".

But at that moment, the people of Wuhan needed those bridges. At the center of the storm, their "want to do something" is only stronger than an "outsider" like me. They also need more courage from each other to confront the storm that is sweeping Wuhan and to prove that the city has not been abandoned.

Standing in the "bridge" between me, for the first time out of the media and social media reports, directly from the epidemic area of the front-line emotions. That night, between busy intervals, one after another medical staff sent a message saying, the driver was contacted, thank you, happy New Year. A paramedic repeatedly thanked me, saying that her biggest concern now was not being able to leave work, but not being able to get to work on time.

There are many more of these emotions, hidden in the sheer volume of travel needs, like the little Easter eggs that the new year's Eve presents us with.

At the same time, the small town in northern Guangdong, where I live, was quiet. One past zero, the sound of firecrackers ringing out to welcome spring blessings, while on the other side, the sound of Qq prompts is still ringing off the hook. The administrators and I have started to divide up the finishing work. Some people handle the new lists, some people file old unclaimed orders.

I was once lost in the distant rescue and the laughter of the Near. But when I went from being a bystander to a participant, finding out what I could do as a human being outside of my professional aspirations, I seemed to understand a little bit about the obsession of the car owners and volunteers who chose to run.

That night, wuhan has issued a new Wuhan Pneumonia Prevention and Control Headquarters Notice (No. 8) to urgently solicit 6,000 taxis across the city to meet residents'travel needs. Someone transferred the news to the group, we all feel that this is a good start, at least that the "closed city" after the supporting has begun to establish.

"Happy New Year! I hope tomorrow is a good day. " The arrival of the zero point so that the New Year's Eve finally have a little presence, the sky administrator said, we began to say happy New Year.

Everyone is thinking that tomorrow will be a new beginning.

Unity of purpose

However, the sudden change almost changed the fate of the travel group.

On the afternoon of January 25, Wuhan issued the new Wuhan Pneumonia Prevention and Control Headquarters Circular No. 9("Order No. 9") , saying that in order to control the risk of infection caused by mobile people, starting from 00:00 on the 26th, in addition to licensed vehicles, motor vehicles are controlled in the central urban area.

This means that private cars are not allowed to drive in the city without permission after midnight. As a result, these caring car owners will be forced to stop travel services, a large number of medical travel mutual help group will usher in the fate of disbanding.


It caught us all off guard. At that time, two groups of health care workers had just been established, their travel needs poured into the chat box, the way smooth operation of the mutual support system, was sent to the hands of car owners. There are many people in the car owners group are asking, really can not run? We're booked up for tomorrow. What are we GONNA do?

The bigger problem is that Wuhan has no updates to its travel system beyond the 6,000 taxis mentioned in the previous decree, and the average allocation of three to five taxis per community is far from enough.

"people in Wuhan are trying to save themselves. Why is the government like this? " Many people realized the problem, and car owners in the group began to vent their anger.

When the administrator of the owner group consoled the owner, he was not sure: "there should be measures, otherwise this is too pit. "

"today may be the last day, go! " Corner said in the administrator's discussion group at the same time. The Sky Replies: "That checks, can succeed to retire best. "

In fact, from the beginning, we know that this kind of love relay way can not really solve the travel of medical staff. It's just trying to give them as much of a transitional period as possible in times of crisis. And in the second day, including me, several managers have started some fatigue, but also reflect on the mutual aid group of Personal Safety, health and epidemic prevention and other potential risks.

After a brief discussion, the corner edited a new bulletin, imploring everyone to "stand the last watch. ". "We will rest at home from midnight tonight and try not to go out and cause any trouble. This is a contribution to our city, " she wrote in the announcement. "We believe that there will be supporting facilities for front-line personnel to travel tomorrow. "

Although the Wuhan government has shown a rather sluggish emergency response capacity in the past few days, and the No. 9 order once brought a sense of frustration to everyone, these Wuhan people who rushed to the front line of "self-help" , there are still many people who believe that the government will find a way to solve the subsequent problems. But at the time, for those of us with limited abilities, there was perhaps no other option than to believe.

While positive signs from all walks of life have helped the people of Wuhan rebuild their confidence, we are also seeing some improvement. The construction of the "Xiaotangshan" model of the Vulcan Mountain and Raytheon Mountain hospitals has begun. Major media outlets are also rolling with material and financial assistance from commercial companies, as well as news that hundreds of military doctors and multiple medical rescue teams are rushing to Wuhan.

In the helpless and hope of interweaving, "stand the last shift" has become the most concrete goal in front of all.

After the release of the new announcement, the administrators made several preparations. The majority of the troops remained in the three groups, collecting and distributing medical travel requirements, stressing to them that travel time should be up to 0pm when the 9th order went into effect. To find out whether the community travel service under Order 8 covered medical staff, we called the Wuhan Traffic Control Bureau all afternoon and sent private messages to the "Wuhan Traffic Police" on Weibo, but no reply was received.

Considering that some of the free food and accommodation assistance could be disguised as medical travel, we called one by one to check on the resources that were circulating widely in the various groups. There are donations from the private materials to find mutual aid group, we also try to help each other docking hospital, find the owner of transport.

That afternoon, the atmosphere of car owners group unprecedented high, car owners in addition to take orders, words also up. "everyone just take care and do your job, " said a Hanyang owner during the discussion. "The rest of US should not make trouble for the government. "

Some car owners who did not approve of the 9 began to look for their own solutions. Some people reported the problem to the Red Cross Society, while others in the group said that he had just called the medical staff who would pick up tomorrow morning, promised to meet the scheduled time to pick her up: "I said if the road was stopped, you will give the police uncle, let them send you home. "

In the evening, some news began to circulate in various travel support groups. A screenshot shows, after consulting the city Traffic Management Bureau, medical staff in 26 after 0:00 can drive, but need to carry and show the name tag. A manager was informed that the provincial headquarters and the city headquarters are still in communication about the definition of vehicles. Later, another owner said in the group that the hospital could issue travel certificates for the vehicles used to transport medical staff, and samples of the certificates were also sent to the group.


What makes it difficult for us is that none of these claims appear in any official channels. You have to go through the network, find the staff of the relevant institutions hard to verify. And until we know for sure, we don't know how to answer the owner's question.

At 7:30 that evening, we finally wait for the official news: 26 after 0:00, the City Public Security Traffic Control Department will be prohibited to pass the vehicle owners, the vehicle did not pass all implementation. This amounts to the repeal of Order 9, which was issued less than four hours ago.

The crisis in the MUTUALS is not entirely over: the official announcement does not mention a more specific definition, and there is no way of knowing what a "closed vehicle" is.


But we didn't have time to think about it, because the "evening rush" began in Florida. Many of the medical trips were in the morning and evening, and many of them were heading to the hospital for the morning shift or waiting for the bus home after an all-night shift, some people just go home to change clothes, ready to go back to the hospital for a long time "camp. ".

Some people bemoan the fact that they still have work to do, while others are glad that they can still run.

It was a little after 10:00 at night, and the owner, Lao Xu, was still on his way. He ran all day with eight doctors today, but he was still a little nervous, not knowing whether his workload was more or less. In the afternoon, when he was stuck in traffic on the Erqi Bridge, he posted a message on his facebook page: "paramedics are so hard. "

Car owner "blue point" and old Xu in the group to cheer each other. Earlier, blue dot ran out of gas to pick up the paramedics, finally found a gas station, did not have time to eat, and began to pick up orders in the group, "filled with gas, happy. "

They were not the only ones on the road that high-spirited night. Some people have run all over the three towns in Wuhan, some people close to midnight, still in the group call after the last one to go home to sleep.

REAKA had to emphasize in the group: "You do not do, please pay attention to the body, or we feel very uncomfortable in the heart, do not collapse. "


Thanks from the medical staff appeared in our chat box, and in a more concrete way on the front of the car owners, as if many of them had secretly left masks, alcohol and other protective equipment on the car, to their owners, who like the Children Found Candy, in the group and other people "show off" up.

"helping each other, thank you very much, " said one owner.

At the stroke of midnight, the order of nine was forgotten. The 500-seat motorist group is already full, and there are still many people waiting to be admitted.

Time out

Behind the high spirits, the crisis is creeping in.

By the third day, the administrators were even more exhausted. We, as information transfer stations, need to keep our eyes on the screen all day, collecting and distributing messages, as well as regularly collating and verifying other information provided by medical care and car owners. Because of the round-the-clock, I was just a family member to chase a few times, and corner busy can only eat instant noodles, there are also their own managers to drive orders, simply do not have time to rest.

We don't want to stop, but we don't know how much longer we can hold out.

Fortunately, a few programmers to find corner, proposed to travel mutual group to do a small program, so that the operation of Health Care Group fully automated. Programmers are very motivated, only two days to make a prototype, but also perfect and wait for platform review, will not help for a while.

As a loosely organized group assembled on a temporary basis, our problems go far beyond that.

Although the owners are still very enthusiastic in the group, but we know that they behind the screen in these two days experienced from the material to the spirit of the huge consumption.

They don't get paid, they go out for days at a time, and they pay for gas by the hundreds and thousands. Protective supplies are also bought by themselves, these materials are quickly consumed, and at that time Wuhan is experiencing the rapid spread of the epidemic, even hospitals have begun to ask for social assistance because of the shortage of materials, and ordinary people can how much?

We have also looked at more organized convoys, or ones that are run by professional charities that can supply alcohol and masks to owners and require them to disinfect on time, but we clearly do not have the capacity to do so. First, car owners are to take orders in the form of spontaneity, decentralization is too strong; second, we also worry that in the absence of a unified management of car owners, it is difficult to be absolutely fair and infallible in the distribution.

We dare not rashly accept the society donates the material and the fund, can only repeatedly emphasize must pay attention to the individual protection. But later, one of the owners told us that he had developed fever and had gone home to quarantine himself. We don't think we can protect the people on the front lines.

The situation for the owner of the car is more serious than expected, and not everyone can understand their good deeds. Some car owners were busy picking up and dropping off medical staff outside on New Year's Eve. They came home that night and had an argument with their families. There was also a car owner who said in the group that his car keys had been taken away by his family and he could no longer take orders, decided to quit the group for fear of taking up a place in the group.

Encounter material shortage, physical and mental exhaustion of their choice to leave, it is human nature, no one will blame them. But the owner in the retreat before the crowd, or solemnly tunnel a "sorry. ".

In the face of numerous contradictions, the car owners left also began to examine the "bridge" of the fragile and uncertain future.

The night before, the owner of the old Xu to the administrator, "Zuoweimen" called up to a quarter of an hour. "He said we are not regular army and we can't do proper disinfection and safety measures. If one person is infected, there will be a chain reaction. "

"You must give the answer today. " Hung up the phone, old Xu sent him a message, "others drag, we can not drag. "

Old Xu's words stung everyone's nerves. No one wants to see these good people exposed to danger, and no one can afford such endless consumption. In the end, we decided to suspend the medical travel support group for an indefinite period starting at 00:00 on the 27th.


"Our intention was to go through a gap, " Jiao wrote in the evening's announcement, "people come from all walks of life and all the administrators on the team are assembled in a group on an ad hoc basis. We have not been able to provide the full range of services for everyone. "

We're not the only ones who are confused. A few days ago, a civilian team leader wrote in the narrative, his team in the past few days, the number of drivers from 4,000 rapidly fell to 400: "The whole team has really reached the end of the stick. "

After the group break, we still wanted to do something for the owners and the paramedics, as Cape Horn put it in the bulletin, "do what we can. "

To find a way out, we've tried to hook up our support groups to more professional charities or to ride-hailing platforms. Because the organization or the platform can provide the vehicle owner with the more specialized protective equipment.

After seeing the news that Didi had assembled 100 drivers to form a "medical protection team, " Reaka came up with the idea of seeking help from the platform, and finally contacted Didi through online customer service, telephone customer service consultation and the help of Weibo big V's, but at the time, the latter only had limited coverage in Xiehe, Wuhan Central Hospital and three hospitals in Wuhan.

The number of drivers in the health care team has increased to 200, shifting from manual deployment to platform deployment, but it will take time to serve more health care workers, Didi chuxing President Liu Qingfa said on Weibo on Thursday. "please give us a moment, " Liu wrote.

We have also tried, with the help of the media, to provide free accommodation for medical staff. But today (January 31) , the Wuhan Medical Hotel Support Alliance announced that due to lack of materials and funds, the hotel operation has reached its limit, medical staff and guests will no longer be served at 159 hotels, bed-and-breakfast, apartments and small chain hotels in Wuhan.

In the face of disaster, there is a limit to what even the commercial forces that can marshal vast resources can do. But what if even platforms can not help, and what happens to temporary, self-motivated, self-organizing support groups like ours? No one's telling US anything.

Didi chuxing: Please give us some time

Many of the owners are still active on the front lines. Including Lao Xu, they began to receive orders through other channels such as wechat group, not only to transport medical care, but also transport supplies. "Even if the suspension, we are not trying to take orders, it is better to continue, " a car owner said in a private chat.

At that time, medical travel service to pick up the order tool has emerged, I was in a few other more relaxed wechat group, car owners began to call on people to use these platforms. A paramedic told us we finally got a community service. Didi contacted us, hoping to dock with the owners of the cars in the group.

Things seem to be slowly moving in a better direction, and no one is talking about restarting the support group.

There have been media reports about caring car owners, they are portrayed as Wuhan's civilian heroes, linked to the isolated city of the capillary, but I still do not know how to write about them. I don't want to glorify ordinary people as heroes, because to be a hero means that their sacrifice and efforts will be justified by the glorification.

The so-called unity of purpose, only by the short-term connection between people is not enough. In the face of a sudden disaster, the People's power quickly gathered in the way of self-burning, although it can create a miracle for a short time, but because of the lack of unified deployment and resources to support, after the miracle, there is no end to the road, with all the good people who are overwhelmed.

And running to save the Wuhan people, by no means flat "good people and good deeds" template. The choice between people is always complicated and multi-faceted. Before Wuhan closed the Han passage, they were just ordinary people who didn't know each other. They also had their own life, fatigue and fear, and also had a distance out of reach.

On the morning of the 28th, old Xu suddenly said he would like to tell me a good news, as he was enrolled into the community volunteer team, and the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission asked him to report tomorrow at 10 am. That day, nearly 6,000 coronaviruses were confirmed nationwide. Bryant's sudden death had long saddened the old fan, but he quickly traveled around Wuhan, looking for every opportunity to transport supplies and medical care.

The night before, old Xu had slept only two hours. "Wuhan, get well soon, " he wrote in his circle of friends

REAKA, Horn, firmament, Saemon, blue dot, old Xu

Unity of purpose

However, the sudden change almost changed the fate of the travel group.

On the afternoon of January 25, Wuhan issued the new Wuhan Pneumonia Prevention and Control Headquarters Circular No. 9("Order No. 9") , saying that in order to control the risk of infection caused by mobile people, starting from 00:00 on the 26th, in addition to licensed vehicles, motor vehicles are controlled in the central urban area.

This means that private cars are not allowed to drive in the city without permission after midnight. As a result, these caring car owners will be forced to stop travel services, a large number of medical travel mutual help group will usher in the fate of disbanding.

Time out

Behind the high spirits, the crisis is creeping in.

By the third day, the administrators were even more exhausted. We, as information transfer stations, need to keep our eyes on the screen all day, collecting and distributing messages, as well as regularly collating and verifying other information provided by medical care and car owners. Because of the round-the-clock, I was just a family member to chase a few times, and corner busy can only eat instant noodles, there are also their own managers to drive orders, simply do not have time to rest.

We don't want to stop, but we don't know how much longer we can hold out.

Fortunately, a few programmers to find corner, proposed to travel mutual group to do a small program, so that the operation of Health Care Group fully automated. Programmers are very motivated, only two days to make a prototype, but also perfect and wait for platform review, will not help for a while.

As a loosely organized group assembled on a temporary basis, our problems go far beyond that.

Although the owners are still very enthusiastic in the group, but we know that they behind the screen in these two days experienced from the material to the spirit of the huge consumption.

They don't get paid, they go out for days at a time, and they pay for gas by the hundreds and thousands. Protective supplies are also bought by themselves, these materials are quickly consumed, and at that time Wuhan is experiencing the rapid spread of the epidemic, even hospitals have begun to ask for social assistance because of the shortage of materials, and ordinary people can how much?

We have also looked at more organized convoys, or ones that are run by professional charities that can supply alcohol and masks to owners and require them to disinfect on time, but we clearly do not have the capacity to do so. First, car owners are to take orders in the form of spontaneity, decentralization is too strong; second, we also worry that in the absence of a unified management of car owners, it is difficult to be absolutely fair and infallible in the distribution.

We dare not rashly accept the society donates the material and the fund, can only repeatedly emphasize must pay attention to the individual protection. But later, one of the owners told us that he had developed fever and had gone home to quarantine himself. We don't think we can protect the people on the front lines.

The situation for the owner of the car is more serious than expected, and not everyone can understand their good deeds. Some car owners were busy picking up and dropping off medical staff outside on New Year's Eve. They came home that night and had an argument with their families. There was also a car owner who said in the group that his car keys had been taken away by his family and he could no longer take orders, decided to quit the group for fear of taking up a place in the group.

Encounter material shortage, physical and mental exhaustion of their choice to leave, it is human nature, no one will blame them. But the owner in the retreat before the crowd, or solemnly tunnel a "sorry. ".

In the face of numerous contradictions, the car owners left also began to examine the "bridge" of the fragile and uncertain future.

The night before, the owner of the old Xu to the administrator, "Zuoweimen" called up to a quarter of an hour. "He said we are not regular army and we can't do proper disinfection and safety measures. If one person is infected, there will be a chain reaction. "

"You must give the answer today. " Hung up the phone, old Xu sent him a message, "others drag, we can not drag. "

Old Xu's words stung everyone's nerves. No one wants to see these good people exposed to danger, and no one can afford such endless consumption. In the end, we decided to suspend the medical travel support group for an indefinite period starting at 00:00 on the 27th.

Some car owners were busy picking up and dropping off medical staff outside on New Year's Eve. They came home that night and had an argument with their families. There was also a car owner who said in the group that his car keys had been taken away by his family and he could no longer take orders, decided to quit the group for fear of taking up a place in the group.

Encounter material shortage, physical and mental exhaustion of their choice to leave, it is human nature, no one will blame them. But the owner in the retreat before the crowd, or solemnly tunnel a "sorry. ".

In the face of numerous contradictions, the car owners left also began to examine the "bridge" of the fragile and uncertain future.

The night before, the owner of the old Xu to the administrator, "Zuoweimen" called up to a quarter of an hour. "He said we are not regular army and we can't do proper disinfection and safety measures. If one person is infected, there will be a chain reaction. "

"You must give the answer today. " Hung up the phone, old Xu sent him a message, "others drag, we can not drag. "

Old Xu's words stung everyone's nerves. No one wants to see these good people exposed to danger, and no one can afford such endless consumption. In the end, we decided to suspend the medical travel support group for an indefinite period starting at 00:00 on the 27th.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Our intention was to go through a gap, " Jiao wrote in the evening's announcement, "people come from all walks of life and all the administrators on the team are assembled in a group on an ad hoc basis. We have not been able to provide the full range of services for everyone. "

We're not the only ones who are confused. A few days ago, a civilian team leader wrote in the narrative, his team in the past few days, the number of drivers from 4,000 rapidly fell to 400: "The whole team has really reached the end of the stick. "

After the group break, we still wanted to do something for the owners and the paramedics, as Cape Horn put it in the bulletin, "do what we can. "

To find a way out, we've tried to hook up our support groups to more professional charities or to ride-hailing platforms. Because the organization or the platform can provide the vehicle owner with the more specialized protective equipment.

After seeing the news that Didi had assembled 100 drivers to form a "medical protection team, " Reaka came up with the idea of seeking help from the platform, and finally contacted Didi through online customer service, telephone customer service consultation and the help of Weibo big V's, but at the time, the latter only had limited coverage in Xiehe, Wuhan Central Hospital and three hospitals in Wuhan.

The number of drivers in the health care team has increased to 200, shifting from manual deployment to platform deployment, but it will take time to serve more health care workers, Didi chuxing President Liu Qingfa said on Weibo on Thursday. "please give us a moment, " Liu wrote.

We have also tried, with the help of the media, to provide free accommodation for medical staff. But today (January 31) , the Wuhan Medical Hotel Support Alliance announced that due to lack of materials and funds, the hotel operation has reached its limit, medical staff and guests will no longer be served at 159 hotels, bed-and-breakfast, apartments and small chain hotels in Wuhan.

In the face of disaster, there is a limit to what even the commercial forces that can marshal vast resources can do. But what if even platforms can not help, and what happens to temporary, self-motivated, self-organizing support groups like ours? No one's telling US anything.

Didi chuxing: Please give us some time

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Many of the owners are still active on the front lines. Including Lao Xu, they began to receive orders through other channels such as wechat group, not only to transport medical care, but also transport supplies. "Even if the suspension, we are not trying to take orders, it is better to continue, " a car owner said in a private chat.

At that time, medical travel service to pick up the order tool has emerged, I was in a few other more relaxed wechat group, car owners began to call on people to use these platforms. A paramedic told us we finally got a community service. Didi contacted us, hoping to dock with the owners of the cars in the group.

Things seem to be slowly moving in a better direction, and no one is talking about restarting the support group.

There have been media reports about caring car owners, they are portrayed as Wuhan's civilian heroes, linked to the isolated city of the capillary, but I still do not know how to write about them. I don't want to glorify ordinary people as heroes, because to be a hero means that their sacrifice and efforts will be justified by the glorification.

The so-called unity of purpose, only by the short-term connection between people is not enough. In the face of a sudden disaster, the People's power quickly gathered in the way of self-burning, although it can create a miracle for a short time, but because of the lack of unified deployment and resources to support, after the miracle, there is no end to the road, with all the good people who are overwhelmed.

And running to save the Wuhan people, by no means flat "good people and good deeds" template. The choice between people is always complicated and multi-faceted. Before Wuhan closed the Han passage, they were just ordinary people who didn't know each other. They also had their own life, fatigue and fear, and also had a distance out of reach.

On the morning of the 28th, old Xu suddenly said he would like to tell me a good news, as he was enrolled into the community volunteer team, and the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission asked him to report tomorrow at 10 am. That day, nearly 6,000 coronaviruses were confirmed nationwide. Bryant's sudden death had long saddened the old fan, but he quickly traveled around Wuhan, looking for every opportunity to transport supplies and medical care.

The night before, old Xu had slept only two hours. "Wuhan, get well soon, " he wrote in his circle of friends
